<p>Foster care nondiscrimination laws protect LGBTQ foster parents and families from discrimination by foster care agencies and officials. Some states permit state-licensed child welfare agencies to refuse to place and provide services to children and families, including LGBTQ people and same-sex couples, if doing so conflicts with their religious beliefs.</p>

<p><img src="./FosterCareLaws.png" alt="./FosterCareLaws.png" width="100%" /></p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">TX may deny to consent to share data or treat a foster child, based on the sincere religious beliefs of the clinician</code></p>

